WEBVTT

00:02.377 --> 00:05.995
Given her abrupt drop
in blood pressure and pulse...

00:06.215 --> 00:08.251
...| diagnosed a placental abruption.

00:08.467 --> 00:11.209
We performed a successful
emergency C-section.

00:11.386 --> 00:14.594
She was having chest pains,
shortness of breath.

00:14.765 --> 00:17.973
The classic symptoms of
an amniotic fluid embolism.

00:18.143 --> 00:20.384
Her lungs were no longer functioning.

00:20.604 --> 00:22.720
I had to get her to a trauma unit.

00:22.940 --> 00:24.271
We were losing her.

00:24.483 --> 00:27.600
-And she went into arrest.
-That's enough.

00:29.279 --> 00:32.146
I kept her alive long enough
to become a mother.

00:32.866 --> 00:35.448
What a desperate thing to say.

00:36.662 --> 00:38.368
I don't want to die.

00:39.873 --> 00:42.455
Everyone dies someday.

00:43.627 --> 00:46.369
[m1

01:22.457 --> 01:24.448
[m1

01:31.967 --> 01:34.629
Time to go, Mr. Red. Time to go.

01:34.803 --> 01:36.668
No, no, no. Not yet.

01:36.847 --> 01:39.338
I want another one. I want another one.

01:39.516 --> 01:41.177
-I paid. I want another.
-No. You go.

01:41.393 --> 01:44.055
It's Friday. It's too long for you.

01:44.271 --> 01:45.932
You go.

01:47.357 --> 01:51.225
[RAYMOND COUGHING]

02:11.715 --> 02:13.330
Mr. Red?

02:36.281 --> 02:39.023
[TIRES SCREECHING
AND HONK HONKING]

02:48.377 --> 02:49.958
You trying to get yourself killed?

02:57.052 --> 02:58.963
Cape May.

03:00.639 --> 03:02.630
Cape May, New Jersey.

03:02.808 --> 03:04.218
That's 200 miles away.

03:12.943 --> 03:14.808
Cape May it is.

03:15.195 --> 03:17.356
[m1

03:32.170 --> 03:33.580
[EKG FLATLINING]

03:34.172 --> 03:35.503
Don't go, Lizzy.

03:35.716 --> 03:37.502
Please, don't go.

03:37.718 --> 03:42.052
[m1

03:46.309 --> 03:47.890
[BABY COOING]

03:48.061 --> 03:49.676
Now go.

03:50.522 --> 03:52.012
And stay away from us.

03:54.443 --> 03:56.308
RAYMOND:
Everyone dies someday.

03:57.779 --> 03:59.644
You say something?

04:04.369 --> 04:05.529
RAYMOND:
Marvin, it's Raymond.

04:05.746 --> 04:08.704
I'm taking a leave
of indeterminate length.

04:09.166 --> 04:11.498
Suspend all transactions.

04:11.710 --> 04:15.373
Pay off all my outstanding debt.

04:15.589 --> 04:19.127
If you need additional funds
to cover any shortfall...

04:19.301 --> 04:21.292
...execute a wire transfer
from Barbados.

04:21.470 --> 04:24.428
Dembe has a "power of attorney"
letter on file...

04:24.598 --> 04:27.431
...should a signature be necessary.

04:39.529 --> 04:41.861
-How much for the cab?
-No, you're good.

04:42.032 --> 04:44.614
No, no.
How much do you want for the cab?

04:44.826 --> 04:46.657
You're kidding, right?

04:53.668 --> 04:55.329
That's plenty.

05:05.263 --> 05:06.673
RAYMOND:
Thank you.

05:18.109 --> 05:22.227
[m1

06:03.989 --> 06:05.980
[WIND CHIMES TINKLING]

06:15.834 --> 06:17.370
[DOOR BANGING]

06:29.097 --> 06:31.679
[m1

07:43.380 --> 07:45.541
[m1

08:09.698 --> 08:11.108
Hey.

08:13.660 --> 08:15.275
Hey!

08:16.329 --> 08:17.865
No!

08:18.039 --> 08:19.700
Stop!

08:21.459 --> 08:23.370
[m1

09:09.215 --> 09:11.297
[GRUNTING]

09:13.970 --> 09:15.301
[COUGHING]

09:20.393 --> 09:22.349
[WOMAN GASPING]

09:25.690 --> 09:28.397
[m1

10:00.475 --> 10:02.090
RAYMOND:
I'll find a blanket.

10:10.235 --> 10:11.975
[BELL DINGS]

10:13.571 --> 10:15.562
May | help you?

10:59.701 --> 11:01.532
You're okay.

11:03.371 --> 11:05.202
Talk to me.

11:08.209 --> 11:10.621
It's not that he died.

11:11.087 --> 11:15.296
It's not even the way he died.

11:16.092 --> 11:19.209
It's that the things I said to him...

11:19.387 --> 11:21.218
...just...

11:21.931 --> 11:24.798
...before he died....

11:34.903 --> 11:40.239
[m1

12:17.195 --> 12:18.810
Hello?

12:22.742 --> 12:24.778
[m1

12:32.669 --> 12:33.749
RAYMOND:
You okay?

12:37.006 --> 12:38.917
There's someone here.

12:39.092 --> 12:40.832
Outside.

12:43.346 --> 12:45.257
He's here to kill me.

12:45.431 --> 12:47.592
There. There he is.

12:48.726 --> 12:50.682
See his shadow?

12:53.815 --> 12:55.646
RAYMOND:
Stay away from the window.

13:00.113 --> 13:03.981
[m1

13:04.784 --> 13:06.775
[WIND CHIMES TINKLING]

13:09.080 --> 13:10.695
[CREAKING]

13:46.993 --> 13:48.858
[GRUNTING]

13:49.078 --> 13:51.660
[m1

13:53.541 --> 13:54.621
[WOMAN GASPS]

13:54.792 --> 13:56.328
I found the intruder.

13:57.045 --> 14:00.629
He put up a fight.
I had no choice but to kill him.

14:02.175 --> 14:03.460
You must think I'm crazy.

14:06.429 --> 14:07.919
No.

14:09.265 --> 14:12.632
[m1

14:27.367 --> 14:28.903
We'll have hot water soon.

14:29.118 --> 14:30.824
WOMAN:
There's wine.

14:30.995 --> 14:32.371
And I can make a risotto.

14:55.311 --> 14:58.348
[m1

15:08.950 --> 15:11.532
[m1

15:27.677 --> 15:29.838
Do you think
we'll have hot water tonight?

15:30.054 --> 15:33.296
By the time we finish dinner,
it should be hot.

15:39.772 --> 15:41.182
This is superb.

15:42.442 --> 15:44.182
The rice is just right.

15:44.944 --> 15:47.856
Canned mushrooms. Best I could do.

15:48.448 --> 15:50.154
It's excellent.

15:52.618 --> 15:54.609
You aren't hungry.

15:54.787 --> 15:56.698
[ELECTRICITY CRACKLING]

15:58.166 --> 16:00.407
Who's trying to kill you?

16:02.462 --> 16:05.704
Does it have something to do
with what you told me before?

16:06.132 --> 16:07.212
I'm sorry?

16:07.842 --> 16:09.298
You said you lost someone.

16:09.469 --> 16:12.461
Harsh words were spoken,
words you regret.

16:13.014 --> 16:16.131
l was out of my mind.
There was no one.

16:16.434 --> 16:17.799
Just me.

16:19.562 --> 16:21.098
You don't have to lie.

16:21.564 --> 16:23.475
Neither do you.

16:24.567 --> 16:26.853
You're no hungrier than I am.

16:27.612 --> 16:29.773
You're not enjoying
a single bite of that.

16:30.448 --> 16:32.530
-I told you this is--
-Superb.

16:32.700 --> 16:36.739
The quality of the cooking is
wholly irrelevant in this case, isn't it?

16:37.747 --> 16:39.738
Given the circumstances.

16:40.208 --> 16:42.824
-And those are?
-You tell me.

16:43.336 --> 16:45.122
Tell yourself.

16:45.713 --> 16:47.624
Say it out loud.

16:50.885 --> 16:53.171
It was a Hobson's choice.

16:54.347 --> 16:57.180
There was a woman and her child.

16:58.893 --> 17:00.884
Both were doomed.

17:01.646 --> 17:03.853
Both would die.

17:06.275 --> 17:07.981
lcould...

17:08.152 --> 17:12.612
...either save one or lose both.

17:14.158 --> 17:16.399
I chose the child.

17:20.581 --> 17:22.162
It was....

17:23.167 --> 17:26.876
It was the worst thing
I've ever had to do in my life.

17:27.547 --> 17:29.754
Worst thing by far.

17:32.802 --> 17:34.542
You didn't have a choice.

17:37.098 --> 17:39.305
There's always a choice.

17:41.769 --> 17:43.009
l was arrogant.

17:43.604 --> 17:45.435
l presumed that there was...

17:46.023 --> 17:48.639
...an order to things. That there was--

17:48.818 --> 17:52.652
That if I nourished and protected...

17:52.822 --> 17:56.440
...and taught the child, she would be...

17:57.076 --> 17:58.907
...safe...

18:00.371 --> 18:01.827
...and happy.

18:03.666 --> 18:05.531
And she was neither.

18:07.920 --> 18:11.458
No matter what I tried to do,
all I brought her was misery and violence.

18:11.632 --> 18:13.793
-And eventually--
-Death.

18:16.304 --> 18:17.794
Yes.

18:20.266 --> 18:22.302
And now you're dead.

18:23.603 --> 18:25.935
You believe there's nothing
left for you.

18:26.105 --> 18:27.766
[m1

18:27.940 --> 18:29.646
It's that obvious?

18:30.234 --> 18:32.566
Nothing about you is obvious.

18:38.701 --> 18:40.566
What brought you here?

18:41.996 --> 18:44.578
I honestly don't know.

18:46.250 --> 18:48.366
You've been here before.

18:52.048 --> 18:54.755
Once, a long time ago.

18:56.886 --> 18:59.753
l was a very different person then.

19:00.973 --> 19:02.429
You?

19:03.851 --> 19:05.261
[KNOCKING ON DOOR]

19:08.105 --> 19:09.811
[KNOCKING ON DOOR]

19:11.942 --> 19:14.194
[DOORBELL BUZZING]

19:17.573 --> 19:19.780
[DOORBELL BUZZING]

19:31.337 --> 19:33.669
What can I do for you,
Officer Duncan?

19:34.131 --> 19:37.214
We got a call from a neighbor.
He noticed lights inside.

19:37.385 --> 19:39.842
Oh, yeah.
I was afraid that might happen.

19:40.012 --> 19:42.799
That's why the candles.
Didn't want to alarm anyone.

19:43.140 --> 19:44.971
I take it you're not trespassing.

19:45.142 --> 19:46.348
Oh, good God, no.

19:46.519 --> 19:49.807
Jack and Ida are old family friends.
Offered the place for the weekend.

19:50.147 --> 19:52.183
Mind showing some identification?

19:52.400 --> 19:54.106
No problem. I'll be right back.

19:54.276 --> 19:56.062
If you don't mind,
I'd prefer waiting inside.

19:56.237 --> 19:58.193
RAYMOND: Of course. My mistake.
-lt's a bit chilly.

19:58.364 --> 20:00.229
Wait here. I'll get my ID.

20:10.835 --> 20:14.828
I'm sorry you had to come
all the way out here on such a cold night.

20:21.262 --> 20:24.095
-Didn't mention you had a friend.
-Yeah. My wife, Abigail.

20:24.265 --> 20:26.130
She's feeling
a little under the weather.

20:26.308 --> 20:28.799
-Didn't touch a bite, it looks like.
-No.

20:29.019 --> 20:30.884
I can go and wake her, if you'd like.

20:31.063 --> 20:33.975
No. No, that's okay.
Everything appears in order.

20:35.401 --> 20:37.983
You said you're a friend
of Jack and Ida's.

20:38.279 --> 20:40.645
Yes, I said I was a friend.

20:40.823 --> 20:43.610
Poor Jack.
Miss the hell out of that man.

20:44.160 --> 20:45.991
Yeah, yeah. It's a crying shame.

20:47.329 --> 20:51.868
lda just hasn't been able to
keep the place up since he passed.

20:54.920 --> 20:56.831
Enjoy your stay, Mr. Donnelly.

20:57.047 --> 20:58.708
Thank you, officer.

21:02.845 --> 21:04.381
WOMAN:
He knows.

21:06.140 --> 21:07.801
I don't think so.

21:08.309 --> 21:10.595
He'd have to be very good at hiding it.

21:11.979 --> 21:12.968
We'll see.

21:13.689 --> 21:15.304
Water should be hot.

21:25.242 --> 21:26.448
[SIGHS]

21:29.038 --> 21:30.949
How did you know Jack was dead?

21:32.208 --> 21:34.915
I didn't say he was dead.
I said I missed him.

21:35.628 --> 21:37.835
Still, why would you miss him?

21:39.048 --> 21:41.255
State of the place.

21:42.176 --> 21:46.715
Hasn't been maintained. A man
wouldn't let that happen if he was around.

21:46.889 --> 21:48.470
You said "poor Jack"?

21:48.933 --> 21:50.719
"Jack's Shack."

21:51.393 --> 21:53.520
He took pride in that.

21:54.021 --> 21:58.139
Decorated it, carved his name on it.
It's falling apart.

21:58.859 --> 22:01.726
I figured he was either sick or dead.

22:02.154 --> 22:03.894
Could have been Ida.

22:04.365 --> 22:06.321
I went with Jack.

22:07.326 --> 22:10.489
Men don't usually last
as long as women.

22:10.871 --> 22:12.577
You sound like an actuary.

22:13.707 --> 22:15.868
lam, in a way.

22:21.257 --> 22:22.713
Have you ever killed anyone?

22:24.510 --> 22:28.048
-That's an odd question.
-Have you?

22:29.098 --> 22:30.634
Yes.

22:32.226 --> 22:33.807
Many.

22:34.520 --> 22:37.227
But never anyone
who didn't deserve it.

22:38.649 --> 22:40.310
Me too.

22:41.861 --> 22:43.351
I know.

22:44.780 --> 22:46.190
How?

22:47.867 --> 22:51.200
There aren't a lot of us.
You learn to recognize it.

22:56.500 --> 22:57.910
Yes.

22:58.252 --> 22:59.788
[GLASS SHATTERING]

23:02.464 --> 23:04.671
[m1

23:19.398 --> 23:21.480
[m1

23:40.836 --> 23:43.293
WOMAN: Behind you.
MAN: Aah!

23:44.924 --> 23:47.791
[GRUNTING]

23:53.307 --> 23:55.798
[WOMAN GRUNTING]

24:00.731 --> 24:02.312
[RAYMOND COUGHING]

24:05.527 --> 24:08.064
-You all right?
-Yeah.

24:08.864 --> 24:10.365
Thank you.

24:13.535 --> 24:16.663
-You know him?
-It doesn't matter. He's one of them.

24:16.830 --> 24:18.661
Not the first, not the last.

24:18.874 --> 24:21.911
[m1

24:27.424 --> 24:30.257
[m1

24:50.572 --> 24:53.655
[PIANO PLAYING SOFT TUNE]

25:22.730 --> 25:25.062
Why did you go into the water?

25:27.026 --> 25:29.233
What made you decide?

25:31.780 --> 25:34.772
You've never killed anyone
who didn't deserve it.

25:35.159 --> 25:38.026
Yes. That is a fine thing.

25:38.829 --> 25:40.444
A noble thing.

25:40.998 --> 25:43.080
But not terribly difficult.

25:44.918 --> 25:46.624
That's true.

25:49.339 --> 25:52.627
WOMAN: Have you ever spared
someone who deserved to die?

25:56.472 --> 25:58.463
There was a woman I loved.

26:00.059 --> 26:01.845
She was...

26:03.896 --> 26:05.636
...my life.

26:07.483 --> 26:09.223
My heart.

26:14.281 --> 26:16.067
And she died.

26:17.743 --> 26:20.155
She left behind a little girl.

26:20.329 --> 26:25.039
One last, precious piece of herself.

26:25.542 --> 26:29.330
-She'l| need protection.
TOM: Only if you're in her life.

26:30.130 --> 26:31.540
Go.

26:32.299 --> 26:33.800
Stay away.

26:34.593 --> 26:37.505
I won't let you make
the same mistake with her...

26:38.680 --> 26:40.841
...that you made with Liz.

26:42.601 --> 26:46.435
I would give anything
to be a part of that child's life...

26:47.856 --> 26:53.351
...but a man made it clear
I would never see her...

26:54.071 --> 26:56.153
...hold her...

26:57.157 --> 26:59.273
...watch her grow.

27:03.038 --> 27:06.201
I knew in that moment...

27:06.375 --> 27:12.621
...I would never be any part
of that beautiful little girl's life.

27:14.925 --> 27:16.461
Becauseun

27:18.137 --> 27:20.128
He was her father.

27:23.142 --> 27:27.101
And to harm him
would be to harm her.

27:29.189 --> 27:31.180
A mortal sin.

27:32.442 --> 27:34.603
Her mother is gone.

27:36.071 --> 27:39.063
The father is what she has left
in the world.

27:41.577 --> 27:43.442
Her father.

27:44.830 --> 27:46.320
Yes.

27:47.833 --> 27:49.073
[CELL PHONE VIBRATING]

27:52.421 --> 27:55.663
MAN [ON PHONE]: Gregory,
do you copy? Did you copy that?

28:00.053 --> 28:02.544
We don't have much time.
They're coming.

28:03.098 --> 28:05.510
[m1

28:13.442 --> 28:15.103
RAYMOND:
This'll work.

28:19.239 --> 28:20.820
I'II drive.

28:24.995 --> 28:26.656
I'm not leaving without you.

28:26.997 --> 28:30.160
-Yes, you are.
-No, I'm not.

28:30.334 --> 28:32.495
Those men are after me.
It's not your problem.

28:32.669 --> 28:35.251
You made it my problem
when you walked into the ocean.

28:35.422 --> 28:37.754
I didn't ask for your help. Let me go.

28:38.258 --> 28:39.338
No.

28:39.718 --> 28:42.630
Why not?
What difference does it make to you?

28:43.513 --> 28:45.549
Ever seen the aftermath
of a suicide bombing?

28:45.766 --> 28:47.176
-We're wasting time.
-lhave.

28:47.351 --> 28:49.558
June 29th, 2003.

28:49.728 --> 28:53.141
l was meeting two associates
at the Marouche restaurant in Tel Aviv.

28:53.315 --> 28:54.805
As my car was pulling up...

28:55.025 --> 28:57.641
...a 20-year-old Palestinian
named Ghazi Safar...

28:57.819 --> 29:00.151
...entered and detonated
a vest wired with C4.

29:00.572 --> 29:02.779
-Let me go.
-The shock wave knocked me flat...

29:02.991 --> 29:05.824
...blew out my eardrums. I couldn't hear.
The smoke--

29:05.994 --> 29:07.575
It was like being unden/vater.

29:07.996 --> 29:09.952
I went inside, a nightmare.

29:10.123 --> 29:12.580
Blood, parts of people.

29:14.378 --> 29:18.212
You could tell where Safar
was standing when the vest blew.

29:18.465 --> 29:23.175
It was like a perfect circle of death.

29:24.805 --> 29:28.548
There was almost nothing left
of the people closest to him.

29:28.934 --> 29:33.268
Seventeen dead, 46 injured.
Blown to pieces.

29:33.438 --> 29:36.430
The closer they were to the bomber,
the more horrific the effect.

29:36.608 --> 29:39.771
WOMAN: Stop.
-That's every suicide.

29:40.946 --> 29:43.062
Every single one.

29:44.866 --> 29:50.031
An act of terror perpetrated against
everyone who's ever known you.

29:50.205 --> 29:52.446
Everyone who's ever loved you.

29:53.208 --> 29:57.747
The people closest to you,
the ones who cherish you...

29:57.921 --> 30:01.960
...are the ones who suffer the most pain,
the most damage.

30:02.134 --> 30:04.090
Why would you do that?

30:04.303 --> 30:06.840
Why would you do that
to people who love you?

30:07.055 --> 30:09.546
l have no choice.

30:10.767 --> 30:12.928
There's always a choice.

30:13.186 --> 30:14.562
Is there?

30:14.730 --> 30:18.188
That little girl,
the one you told me about.

30:18.400 --> 30:20.311
The one whose father you spared.

30:20.610 --> 30:24.569
What would you do if you knew--?
Knew...

30:24.740 --> 30:28.779
...that as long as you drew breath,
as long as you continued to exist...

30:29.161 --> 30:31.197
...her life would be in danger?

30:31.371 --> 30:35.330
She would be hunted
and she would be killed.

30:35.500 --> 30:37.240
What would you do?

30:42.466 --> 30:44.377
What would you do?

30:44.843 --> 30:48.961
My child is being raised
by someone else.

30:50.265 --> 30:52.301
I am her mother...

30:52.726 --> 30:55.593
...and I am death to her.

30:56.146 --> 30:58.762
So this is what I'm doing.

31:01.026 --> 31:03.358
I never wanted this.

31:05.739 --> 31:07.400
I know.

31:08.950 --> 31:10.656
Then go.

31:14.956 --> 31:16.742
I can't.

31:16.958 --> 31:19.916
[m1

31:23.673 --> 31:26.961
[m1

32:06.299 --> 32:07.914
You still have time to go.

32:09.469 --> 32:11.050
I don't know your name.

32:12.222 --> 32:14.258
Don't be ridiculous, Raymond.

32:14.808 --> 32:19.347
[m1

32:23.525 --> 32:27.518
[m1

33:00.395 --> 33:01.510
[GAS HISSING]

33:01.730 --> 33:04.847
[m1

33:22.834 --> 33:25.291
[m1

33:28.632 --> 33:30.247
[KNOCKING]

33:36.598 --> 33:38.805
[m1

34:04.501 --> 34:06.787
[m1

34:20.225 --> 34:22.932
[MAN GRUNTING, THEN SCREAMS]

34:30.193 --> 34:33.230
[m1

34:37.951 --> 34:41.318
[m1

34:52.591 --> 34:56.004
[MAN SCREAMING]

34:58.888 --> 35:01.630
[m1

35:06.813 --> 35:08.769
[BLADE SLICES
AND MAN GRUNTING]

35:18.033 --> 35:20.399
[m1

35:34.799 --> 35:36.915
[MAN GRUNTING]

35:42.265 --> 35:45.803
[m1

35:54.444 --> 35:55.980
[MAN GRUNTING]

36:22.347 --> 36:24.508
[m1

